^B@2^*Bhondo717:^*N|cp||at|I think that is a bit optimistic on Ira's part, but given he thought there might be slam, Ira chose a very good sequence. Ira has 2 choices over my 2@C bid. He knows he wants to play in 4 hearts at least. So, if Ira thinks there is no chance for slam, he should just bid 4@H right away. By bidding 4sf, and then bidding 3@H followed by 4@H, he is telling me he always was intending to play 4@H. But by going more slowly, using 4sf, he is also telling me he is interested in slam. That is the difference between the approach Ira took (slam try) vs. his bidding 4@H right away over 2@C. Basically, it is another application of the principle of "fast arrival", where, the slower you bid, once you are in a game force, the more interested you are in slam.|
