UP|36|PF|Y|cp|8|AT|^B@2^z@3^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|We have 2 issues here. First, the bidding tactics.  stef has an optional 1@H call. she is weak, but her ace of clubs is particularly valuable, and good to show her 5 card suit. So I don't quibble with 1@H, but pass would better. steff has a bad hand, with no redeeming value. The ace of clubs is the only good feature of the hand and the J of spades is of questionable value. anna has an interesting tactical choice. 1@S is certainly descriptive, but one could make a case that 3@D is better tactics. Either bid is fine. the reason modern bidding prefers majors is because it is easier to make game in the majors than minors. But in partials, since game is not likely, showing when you have a fit has value and should often be given priority.|
